Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%can}. Pop into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with
the back of a #fork{} or a #potato masher{}.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onions{2}(trimmed and sliced). Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Add the spring onion, cheese, @chipotle paste{20%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the
beans.

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{}. Mix well.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Add the @chorizo{60%g} to the pan, stir-fry until starting to crisp for
~{2-3%mins}.

Once cooked, remove the chorizo and stir it into the bean mixture.

== Quesadillas ==

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} out on a #board{}.

Spread a little of the bean mix over half of each, leaving a small border round
the edge, then fold the tortillas in half to make half moon shapes.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large frying pan on medium-high heat.

== Cooking Quesadillas ==

When hot, carefully lay the quesadillas in the pan. Fry until golden,
~{2%mins} each side. Turn carefully.

Lightly press down on the quesadillas with a #spatula{} to ensure they stick
together and brown nicely.

> TIP: You may have to do this in batches, adding a little more oil to the pan
> each time.

Once cooked, just cover the quesadillas with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Avocado, Tomato and Rocket Salad ==

While the quesadillas are frying, slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you
reach the stone, turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and
pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the insides onto a board.

Roughly chop the avocado.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In a large bowl, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} with the
@olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing).

Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @wild rocket{40%g}, tomatoes and avocado and toss gently.

Serve the quesadillas alongside plenty of rocket salad. Enjoy!

== Step 1 MOD ==

> If you've opted to add chorizo to your meal, then once you've mashed the beans,
> heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.

> Add the chorizo to the pan and stir-fry for ~{2-3%mins}.

> Once cooked, remove the chorizo and stir it into the bean mixture.